name: killer
title: Killer Cages
statement: Valerio is a big fan of different sudokus, despite being bad at solving them. He is particularly interested in those with killer cages. A killer cage is a region where all the numbers must be distinct and have a certain sum. Valerio wants to get better at sudoku, so he is asking for your advice to improve. He will make you T questions of the following form: Given N and K, is there a unique way to write N as sum of K distinct positive integers?
